P.S.
Technically speaking, and army can travel from any coastal province to any
other coastal province in 6 months, which would imply the following matrix
of times:
                   L  P  B  R  V  C  S
London             X  3  3  1  2  1  1		
Paris              3  X  3  2  3  2  2 
Berlin             3  3  X  2  3  2  1
Rome               1  2  2  X  2  1  1
Vienna             2  3  3  2  X  2  2
Constantinople     1  2  2  1  2  X  1
St. Petersburg     1  2  1  1  2  1  X

Therefore at least 5 of the spies were taking the scenic route, which makes
the puzzle insoluble.

