I actually found the easiest way to do this was to make a grid
like Brian suggested, but fill in the blanks with the number
of days it would take to get from each capitol to every other
one.  Then, knowing that I needed 2 threes, 2 fours, and 1 each
five, six, and seven, only one solution was possible.

On Wednesday , Germany spied on Vienna and Austria spied on Rome.
On Thursday, England spied on Moscow, and Russia spied on London.
On Friday, Italy spied on Paris
On Saturday, Turkey spied on Germany
On Sunday, France spied on Ankara

'Twas much fun, Thanks!

Derrick

